profile_positions.description:
As a project Marketing and Communication Manager, I led the launch of the Kukua na Kuku Impact Cluster project primarily be responsible for promoting consumption of poultry products nationally, a key theme within the impact cluster. 
The objectives being to encourage consumers to consume more poultry related products and engage in poultry farming. 

Responsibilities:
•	Consults with all stakeholders private, public and civil society i.e. members of the Poultry association of Tanzania, poultry sector companies in Tanzania, all other poultry related projects in Tanzania, member so the poultry cluster, learning institutions amongst others;
•	Act as a liaison for Dutch project stakeholders for activities done in Tanzania involving 
•	Develop and deliver a nationwide creative marketing and communication strategy, plan and approach for promotion of consumption of poultry products.  
•	Plan and execute a multi-channel publicity campaign i.e. online social media 
•	Make a digital store of all creative content generated for reporting and backchecking purposes; 
•	Develop annual budgets for all campaigns and implement on the same on time and within budget. 
•	Design, develop and or contract creative content creators to develop content for the campaigns both online and offline. Managing all subcontractors and content creators contracted to develop content for the campaigns;
•	Manage and respond to the comments, suggestions and critic submitted on social media channels with relation to the campaigns; 
•	Ensure consistency in the messaging of the content generated. 
•	Provide bi-weekly reports on the progress and outcomes of the campaigns. Ensure all stakeholders are well informed and support the campaigns creative directions as well as the messaging
